- "stars" refer to articles;
- "admirers" refer to users;
- "brightness" refers to the rating;
- "higher than the average shine" means the rating is greater than the average rating.

- 'Top authors' refers to authors with the highest average ratings;
- 'Published articles' are articles with a status of 'published';
- 'Average rating' is calculated by averaging the ratings of all published articles by each author.

- 'Prolific authors' refers to authors who have written the most articles;
- 'Quills have danced across the pages of many articles' is a metaphor for having written a large number of articles;
- 'Literary garden' is a metaphor for the collection of articles and authors.

- Engagement metrics include views, downloads, ratings, and comments;
- The engagement score is the sum of these metrics for each article;
- The relative engagement score is the engagement score divided by the total number of articles;
- The top 5 topics are ranked based on their total engagement scores.

- "Gems" refer to articles that have received high ratings;
- "Highest praise" refers to the highest average ratings;
- "Sparked the most engagement" refers to the articles with the highest share and comment counts.

- "Blossomed into multiple versions" refers to articles that have more than one version;
- "Shared" refers to the number of times an article has been shared;
- "Rated on average" refers to the average rating given to the article.

- "Scribes" refers to authors;
- "Seeds of published wisdom" refers to published articles;
- "Fertile grounds of the North" refers to regions with names containing "North";
- "Years of the recent harvest" refers to the period between January 1, 2020, and December 31, 2022.

- 'Prolific scribes' refers to authors who have written a significant number of articles;
- 'Blossomed into published articles' means the articles have a status of 'published';
- 'Nurtured' refers to the total count of published articles by each author.
